{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UYAAJTxvRmEwuwt78DGpZE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the issue! The `app-user` in the `/app` vhost has:\n- `configure`: empty (no configure permissions)\n- `write`: `.*`\n- `read`: `.*`\n\nThe `configure` permission is empty, which means `app-user` cannot declare (create) queues in the `/app` vhost. Declaring a queue requires the `configure` permission on the queue name.\n\nThe fix is to grant `app-user` full permissions (`.*`) in the `/app` vhost, including the configure permission:\n\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\nThis grants `app-user` the ability to configure, publish, and consume in the `/app` vhost.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":426,"cache_read_input_tokens":29602,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":426},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"318a3b08-3a87-4fb8-8113-52a0251a8c74","uuid":"329b77c0-95af-42c7-b77c-dd9455b03c3f","request_id":"req_011CccxvwdbjfNwGwbjscHQj"}
